Use Raspberry Pi Imager
Choose OS: Raspberry Pi OS Lite (64bit)
Advanced options: Set hostname to something like `bender.local`
Enable ssh and pick a password.
Set wifi settings (if desired)

SSH into the Pi

```bash
ssh pi@bender.local
```

Upgrade what's there:

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y && sudo apt dist-upgrade -y
```

Install Docker and compose

```bash
curl -sSL https://get.docker.com | sh
```

```bash
sudo usermod -aG docker pi
```bash

```bash
DOCKER_CONFIG=${DOCKER_CONFIG:-$HOME/.docker}
```

```bash
mkdir -p $DOCKER_CONFIG/cli-plugins
```

```bash
curl -SL https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/download/v2.4.1/docker-compose-linux-aarch64 -o $DOCKER_CONFIG/cli-plugins/docker-compose
```

```bash
chmod +x $DOCKER_CONFIG/cli-plugins/docker-compose
```

Intstall git to pull the repo:

```bash
sudo apt-get install -y git
```

```bash
git clone https://github.com/collectiveidea/bender.git
```

```bash
cd bender
```

manually copy local .env to ~/bender/.env on the PI

```bash
docker network create caddy
```

```bash
docker compose up -d
```bash

```bash
docker compose run web bin/setup
```

```bash
docker compose run web rake assets:precompile
```